

                            NODE JS / EXPRESS - Server Side Technology
                        -----------------------------------------


                        Basic Commands
                    ---------------------

                1. to create package.json - npm init

                2. Install express - npm i express

                3. Install nodemon - sudo npm i -g nodemon

                4. run the server - node/nodemon index.js

                5. Install jwt token - npm i jsonwebtoken

                6. Install mongoose - npm install mongoose 

                7. install cors - npm i cors






                        Basic Concepts
                    ------------------------

                1. create a folder

                2. create package.json

                3. Create index.js file

                4. Install express

                5 import express in index.js

                6. create app using express

                7. define port number for server app

                8. Install nodemon 

                9. middleware - 

                    9.1 Application specific middleware

                    9.2 Router specific middleware

                10. JWT Token

                    10.1 token generate - sign()

                    10.2 token verify - verify()

                11. Connection between monogoDB and server

                    11.1. Install mongoose 

                    11.2 provide connection string using mongoose

                    11.3 create model 

                    11.4 export model

                12. Solving Asynchronous events

                    12.1 Promise - 
                        12.1.1 resolved state - then()
                        12.1.2 reject state - catch()

                13. cors - cross origin resource shairing protocol

                    13.1 install cors
                    13.2 import cors to index.js
                    13.3 Use the cors in server app